	" Glitches/Techniques
	$LF
]h3
[h4 id=InfiniteFlagGlitch 
	" Infinite Flag Glitch
	$LF
]h4
[div class=p 
	"Looting an enemy drop with a numeric value also locks the amount of the next item pickup to the same value, for a short amount of time.
	$LF
]div
[h4 id=ExecutingCodeAce 
	" Executing Code (ACE)
	$LF
]h4
[div class=p 
	"A more detailed explanation can be found here:
	$LF
]div
[ul 
	[li 
		" In the previous submission 
		(__wikiLink|href=/6610S|implicitdisplaytext=6610S)
		$LF
	]li
	[li 
		" And 
		[a href=https://datacrystal.romhacking.net/wiki/Secret_of_Evermore:Alchemy_RAM_manipulation#TL.3BDR rel=noopener external nofollow 
			"Data Crystal Wiki
		]a
		" for an in depth documentation
		$LF
	]li
]ul
[div class=p 
	"The only difference is that the camera is being possitioned 255*4 pixels to the right, which makes the game read the jump address from the first controller instead of the frame counter.
	$LF
]div
[table 
	[tbody 
		[tr 
			[th 
				"Address
			]th
			[th 
				"Name
			]th
			[th 
				"Value
			]th
			[th 
				"Comment
			]th
		]tr
		[tr 
			[td 
				[code 
					"$7E/3378
				]code
			]td
			[td 
				"Parts of alchemy Slot #0
			]td
			[td 
				[code 
					"$005A
				]code
			]td
			[td 
				"Points at the Camera Offset
			]td
		]tr
		[tr 
			[td 
				[code 
					"$91/005A
				]code
			]td
			[td 
				"Camera Offset (
				[code 
					"LSB Y
				]code
				", 
				[code 
					"MSB X
				]code
				")
			]td
			[td 
				[code 
					"$8104
				]code
			]td
			[td 
				"Points at Controller #1 Copy (Offset 
				[code 
					"$8000
				]code
				")
			]td
		]tr
		[tr 
			[td 
				[code 
					"$91/0104
				]code
			]td
			[td 
				"Controller #1 Copy
			]td
			[td 
				[code 
					"$421A
				]code
			]td
			[td 
				"Points at the Controller Registers (Controller #2)
			]td
		]tr
		[tr 
			[td 
				[code 
					"$91/4218
				]code
			]td
			[td 
				"Controller Register
			]td
			[td 
				[code 
					"$xxxxxxxxxxxxxxxx
				]code
			]td
			[td 
				"The executed code is based on the buttons pressed in the current frame
			]td
		]tr
